		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I edited my last post slightley
<br />
<br />I am not an expert but there are 3 types of mirroring vertical, horizontal and controlled (meaning the mirroring is controlled  by the program) if the mirroring is not set right the display will be jumbled when trying to play through levels but will often still display menus normaly and will outherwise play right, also if the CHR is not correct the display will be even more jumbled

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


